Arizona has been the name of three ships of the United States Navy. 

* , laid down in 1858 and served in the American Civil War.
* , a steam frigate launched in 1865 as the USS Neshaminy. She was renamed twice, carrying the name Arizona for less than three months.
* , a launched in 1915 and sunk by Japanese bombers in the attack on Pearl Harbor 7 December 1941.

